rComments: She's a really kind professor! She'll do whatever she can so that you will pass the class. Make sure to go see her at Office hours so she can recognize you. Her exams are quite difficult but she gives extra credit if you do a homework log. I miss her!
very nice lady, great one on one, not the best lecturer though, go to office hours, she is very fair!

Although Dewey isn't the best lecturer I've had, she made the material understandable Plus the midterms weren't that bad at all. Knowing your equations is half the effort. I started studying off her lectures notes at most two nights before the midterms and final and cramstered the hw, came out with a B+. Not hard at all, just study the notes.

Worst professor ever. Her lectures are confusing and not helpful with the homework, she has difficulty answering questions asked during lecture, says "um" every other word, and never seems to fully understand the material she is teaching. She initially submitted the wrong grade for me. On the plus side, midterms are easier than the practice exams.

Nice lady, but her lectures aren't very clear or helpful in regards to learning the material. Exams are great- she only tests basic understanding of how to do problems. If you do the homework, this class is an easy A.

Very nice lady. Her test are fairly easy. Approachable but her test review material is not very useful. Study the problems online. The homework problems are a good example of what you are expected to know on the exam.
